# Nest.js API

Stack: Nest 10, class-validator/class-transformer DTOs, `@nestjs/jwt`, `@nestjs/throttler`, BullMQ, `helmet`, Prisma.

## Modules

- One module per feature folder (`auth/`, `audit/`, `files/`, `resources/`, ...).
- Wire providers/controllers in `<feature>.module.ts`. Do not import controllers from sibling modules — re-export services instead.
- Register cross-cutting things (guards, interceptors, pipes) globally via `app.module.ts` / `main.ts`.

## Controllers

- Routes under `@Controller("<segment>")`. Keep controllers thin — they validate input and delegate.
- Validate request bodies with **class-validator DTOs** placed next to the controller (`*.dto.ts`).
- Apply `@UseGuards(AuthGuard)` for protected endpoints; admin-only routes use `@RequireAuthRealm("admin")`.
- Throttle login/forgot/reset endpoints with `@Throttle({ default: { limit, ttl } })`.

```ts
@Throttle({ default: { limit: 5, ttl: 60000 } })
@Post("login")
login(@Body() dto: LoginDto) { return this.auth.login(dto.email, dto.password); }
```

## Services

- Inject services with `@Inject(Foo) private readonly foo: Foo`.
- Throw Nest HTTP exceptions (`UnauthorizedException`, `BadRequestException`, ...) — never raw `Error` from a controller path.
- Don't access `req`/`res` directly from services; pass what's needed as params.

## Auth & permissions

- Use the shared realm constants from `@openadminjs/permissions` (`DEFAULT_AUTH_REALM`).
- Permission strings follow `resource.action` (`posts.publish`, `users.create`).

## Background work

- Long jobs go through BullMQ (`@nestjs/bullmq`). Don't `setTimeout` long-running work inside request handlers.
- Queue is optional — code paths must degrade gracefully when `REDIS_URL` is unset.
